---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is open house lead automation?",
    answer:
      "Open house lead automation is a workflow that captures visitor data, segments people by interest and readiness, triggers fast follow-up, and routes stronger opportunities into live agent action.",
  },
  {
    question: "What should be automated first after an open house?",
    answer:
      "Start with structured sign-in capture, same-day follow-up, simple intent-based segmentation, and next-step tasks for high-interest visitors.",
  },
  {
    question: "Why do open house leads get lost so often?",
    answer:
      "They usually get lost because data capture is incomplete, follow-up is delayed, or every visitor receives the same generic message regardless of intent.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can open house follow-up be personalized at scale?",
    answer:
      "Yes. With the right prompts and segmentation, teams can personalize the first messages while keeping the workflow fast and repeatable.",
  },
];
---

<MainLayout
  title="Open House Lead Automation | Realty Efficiency Hub"
  description="Open house lead automation for faster visitor follow-up, better segmentation, stronger qualification, and more post-event appointment conversion."
  image="/images/posts/open-house-lead-automation-cover.webp"
>
  <section class="solution-shell">
    <div class="eyebrow">Solution</div>
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div>
        <h1>Open House Lead Automation</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          Open house lead automation helps real estate agents turn event traffic into structured follow-up instead of post-event chaos.
          The best systems capture visitor data cleanly, follow up the same day, and route the most serious opportunities into live conversations quickly.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="/blog/open-house-lead-automation/" class="primary-link">See the open house workflow guide</a>
          <a href="/blog/open-house-follow-up-prompts/" class="secondary-link">See follow-up prompt examples</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <figure class="hero-visual">
        <img
          src="/images/posts/open-house-lead-automation-cover.webp"
          alt="Open house lead automation workflow visual"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </figure>
    </div>

    <section class="quick-answer">
      <h2>The Short Version</h2>
      <p>
        A useful open house workflow should capture visitor information in one structured way,
        segment attendees by readiness, send fast and relevant follow-up, and create a clear next action
        for anyone showing meaningful buying intent.
      </p>

      <div class="glance-grid">
        <article class="glance-card">
          <h3>Best for</h3>
          <p>Agents or teams running open houses regularly and losing momentum in the first 24 to 72 hours after the event.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="glance-card">
          <h3>Main outcome</h3>
          <p>Better same-day follow-up and more appointments or next-step conversations from open house traffic.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="glance-card">
          <h3>What to automate first</h3>
          <p>Sign-in capture, attendee segmentation, same-day texts or emails, and live task creation for hot leads.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="summary-box">
      <h2>What this solution should improve</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>more reliable capture of visitor details and intent</li>
        <li>faster post-event follow-up timing</li>
        <li>better separation between hot, warm, and low-intent visitors</li>
        <li>stronger conversion from event attendance into appointments</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <h2>How the open house workflow should work</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">
            The goal is simple: make the event-to-follow-up handoff just as strong as the event itself.
          </p>
        </div>
        <img
          class="inline-visual"
          src="/images/posts/open-house-lead-automation-kpi.webp"
          alt="Open house lead automation KPIs"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="steps-grid">
        <article class="step-card">
          <h3>1. Capture clean data</h3>
          <p>Use one sign-in system so names, phone numbers, emails, and buying intent are collected consistently.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="step-card">
          <h3>2. Segment the visitors</h3>
          <p>Hot visitors, curious neighbors, active buyers, and long-cycle prospects should not receive the same next step.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="step-card">
          <h3>3. Follow up fast</h3>
          <p>Same-day follow-up keeps the property and the agent top of mind while event intent is still fresh.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="step-card">
          <h3>4. Route the best opportunities</h3>
          <p>High-intent signals should create live tasks or direct outreach so the strongest leads do not cool off overnight.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Where agents usually get stuck</h2>
      <p>
        Most open house follow-up problems come from weak capture, generic messaging, or no clear rule for who deserves fast live attention.
        That creates missed chances even when attendance looks strong on paper.
      </p>
      <p>
        Open house lead automation works best when the marketing, follow-up, and qualification parts are designed as one workflow.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        {faqs.map((faq) => (
          <article class="faq-item">
            <h3>{faq.question}</h3>
            <p>{faq.answer}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section related">
      <h2>Supporting articles published by March 19, 2026</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/blog/open-house-lead-automation/">Open House Lead Automation Workflow</a>
        <a href="/blog/open-house-follow-up-prompts/">Open House Follow-Up Prompts</a>
        <a href="/blog/open-house-marketing-prompts/">Open House Marketing Prompts</a>
        <a href="/blog/real-estate-follow-up-text-prompts/">Real Estate Follow-Up Text Prompts</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    mainEntity: faqs.map((faq) => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      name: faq.question,
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: faq.answer,
      },
    })),
  })} />

  <style>
    .solution-shell {
      max-width: 980px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 24px 0;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      padding: 6px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: #eef4ff;
      color: #1d4ed8;
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.3fr) minmax(280px, 0.9fr);
      gap: 24px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 16px 0;
      font-size: 50px;
      line-height: 1.04;
      color: #0f172a;
    }

    .intro {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 19px;
      line-height: 1.75;
      color: #475569;
      max-width: 820px;
    }

    .hero-actions {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 24px;
    }

    .primary-link,
    .secondary-link {
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .primary-link {
      background: #2563eb;
      color: #ffffff;
    }

    .secondary-link {
      background: #ffffff;
      border: 1px solid #dbe4ee;
      color: #0f172a;
    }

    .hero-visual,
    .summary-box,
    .quick-answer,
    .section {
      margin: 0 0 22px 0;
      padding: 24px;
      background: #ffffff;
      border: 1px solid #dbe4ee;
      border-radius: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 28px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.05);
    }

    .hero-visual {
      padding: 14px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f8fbff 0%, #ffffff 100%);
    }

    .hero-visual img,
    .inline-visual {
      width: 100%;
      display: block;
      border-radius: 16px;
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 0 0 12px 0;
      font-size: 30px;
      color: #0f172a;
    }

    h3 {
      margin: 0 0 8px 0;
      font-size: 20px;
      color: #0f172a;
    }

    p,
    li {
      color: #475569;
      font-size: 17px;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 20px;
    }

    .glance-grid,
    .steps-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 14px;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      margin-top: 18px;
    }

    .glance-card,
    .step-card,
    .faq-item {
      padding: 18px;
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: #f8fbff;
      border: 1px solid #dbe4ee;
    }

    .glance-card p,
    .step-card p,
    .faq-item p,
    .section-intro {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .faq-item p {
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    .section-head {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(240px, 0.8fr);
      gap: 18px;
      align-items: start;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .faq-list,
    .related-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .related-grid a {
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #1d4ed8;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .related-grid a:hover {
      color: #1e40af;
    }

    @media (max-width: 820px) {
      .hero-grid,
      .section-head {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 40px;
      }

      .intro {
        font-size: 18px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
